Eva Moore https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eva_Moore 0 Eva Moore (9 February 1868 – 27 April 1955) was an English actress. Her career on stage and in film spanned six decades, and she was active in the women's suffrage movement. In her 1923 book of reminiscences, Exits and Entrances, she describes approximately ninety of her roles in plays, but she continued to act on stage until 1945. She also acted in more than two dozen films. Her daughter, Jill Esmond, was the first wife of Laurence Olivier. Eva_Moore ( 9_February_1868 – 27_April_1955 ) was an_English_actress .
